SUMMARY:Thursday Evening Special 26R (A) (20-22mph)
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Bicycle Club (LBC) Meetup\n25-ish mile flat *rolling
 * route.\n\nA spirited club ride leaving every Thursday. The route is the 
 same each week.\n\nDue to the race-like style of this ride\, including pac
 elining at high speeds\, the use of E-bikes is not recommended.\n\nCue she
 et and GPX files: [https://ridewithgps.com/routes/42866619](https://ridewi
 thgps.com/routes/42866619)\n\n\\*occasionally\, additional miles are added
  mid-loop. Please note the start location is NOT Landis Valley Museum.\n\n
 Show & Go (please bring a cue if you are not familiar with the route).\nNo
  Leader (means that this ride will not be cancelled due to weather).\n\nHe
 lmets are mandatory\; No ear buds or audible music playing devices. Please
  bring water\, and a basic repair kit (spare tube\, tire levers\, pump/CO2
  inflator).\n\nTo eliminate passing around a pen and paper waiver\, we enc
 ourage LBC Club membership and Meetup RSVP below to join this ride. RSVP a
 lso allows us to contact you after the ride if needed. If you do not RSVP 
